observations.recommendation:
We recommended and Management agreed that:

a) the Local Chief Executive refrain from granting cash advances for expenses which should be paid thru check under the name of the supplier;

b) the BAC ensure that competitive bidding is conducted in the procurement of goods and services, and resort to alternative mode of procurement only after meeting the prescribed requirements and conditions; 

c) the Municipal Accountant check the completeness of supporting documents before recording the liquidation of cash advances; and 

d) the concerned personnel submit the lacking documents.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
a.	Instruct the concerned offices to fast track the processing of land title, and henceforth, ensure that title or ownership of project sites would be registered in the name of the Municipality;
b.	Instruct the Municipal Accountant to submit all the required documents and justify all noted deficiencies;
c.	Exert all possible efforts to accumulate or earn funds for the water treatment facility of the poultry dressing plant so that early start-up of project operations could be conducted;
d.	Instruct the BAC Secretariat to timely post Notices of Award and to Proceed to the PhilGEPS and Municipality’s website, if any; and
e.	Justify the need for a consultant despite the fact that technical assistance for the project could be provided by DA-NMIS.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
Instruct the concerned offices to fast track the processing of land title, and henceforth, ensure that title or ownership of project sites would be registered in the name of the Municipality;
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to submit all the required documents and justify all noted deficiencies;
Exert all possible efforts to accumulate or earn funds for the water treatment facility of the poultry dressing plant so that early start-up of project operations could be conducted;
Instruct the BAC Secretariat to timely post Notices of Award and to Proceed to the PhilGEPS and Municipality’s website, if any; and
Justify the need for a consultant despite the fact that technical assistance for the project could be provided by DA-NMIS.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive, in coordination with the Sangguniang Bayan, adopt and implement clear and reasonable policies concerning the payment of mobile expenses. The guidelines should include at the least the following:

(a) Officers and employees who will be allowed to claim reimbursements of mobile expenses, together with the justifications why they are allowed;

(b) Mode of payment and required supporting documents;

(c) Mobile expense limit; and

(d) Accounting treatment of any complimentary cellphone units.
